<p><a name="External_links" id="External_links"></a></p>
<h2><span class="editsection">[<a href="/w/index.php?title=Imre_Lakatos&amp;action=edit&amp;section=12" title="Edit section: External links">edit</a>]</span> <span class="mw-headline">External links</span></h2>
<ul>
<li><a href="http://www.lse.ac.uk/collections/lakatos/scienceAndPseudoscience.htm" class="external text" title="http://www.lse.ac.uk/collections/lakatos/scienceAndPseudoscience.htm" rel="nofollow"><i>Science and Pseudoscience</i></a> (including an MP3 audio file) – Lakatos' 1973 <a href="/wiki/Open_University" title="Open University">Open University</a> <a href="/wiki/BBC_Radio" title="BBC Radio">BBC Radio</a> talk on the subject</li>
<li><cite style="font-style:normal" class="" id="CITEREFO.27ConnorRobertson"><a href="/wiki/John_J._O%27Connor_(mathematician)" title="John J. O'Connor (mathematician)" class="mw-redirect">O'Connor, John J.</a>; <a href="/wiki/Edmund_F._Robertson" title="Edmund F. Robertson">Robertson, Edmund F.</a>, <a href="http://www-history.mcs.st-andrews.ac.uk/Biographies/Lakatos.html" class="external text" title="http://www-history.mcs.st-andrews.ac.uk/Biographies/Lakatos.html" rel="nofollow">"Imre Lakatos"</a>, <i><a href="/wiki/MacTutor_History_of_Mathematics_archive" title="MacTutor History of Mathematics archive">MacTutor History of Mathematics archive</a></i></cite><span class="Z3988" title="ctx_ver=Z39.88-2004&amp;rft_val_fmt=info%3Aofi%2Ffmt%3Akev%3Amtx%3Abook&amp;rft.genre=bookitem&amp;rft.btitle=Imre+Lakatos&amp;rft.atitle=%5B%5BMacTutor+History+of+Mathematics+archive%5D%5D&amp;rft.aulast=O%27Connor&amp;rft.aufirst=John+J.&amp;rft.au=O%27Connor%2C+John+J.&amp;rft.au=Robertson%2C+Edmund+F.&amp;rfr_id=info:sid/en.wikipedia.org:Imre_Lakatos"><span style="display: none;">&#160;</span></span></li>
<li><a href="http://muse.jhu.edu/journals/perspectives_on_science/toc/posc14.3.html" class="external text" title="http://muse.jhu.edu/journals/perspectives_on_science/toc/posc14.3.html" rel="nofollow">Lakatos’s Hungarian intellectual background</a> The Autumn 2006 MIT Press journal <i>Perspectives on Science</i> devoted to articles on this topic, with article abstracts.</li>
</ul>
